    window.open(url,'_blank');
  });
});
</script>
	</div>	</div></div><p>“The lesson here is that in a crisis of this sort, where people are fearful, they don’t look at the government the same way they do under normal circumstances,” says Mr. Voss. “It’s not about ideology right now.”</p><p><i>Editor’s note: As a public service, we’ve removed the paywall </i><i><a href="https://www.csmonitor.com/World/Topics/coronavirus-all-coverage" target="_blank" rel="noopener">for all our coronavirus coverage</a></i><i>. It’s free.</i></p>

